PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1772471476
OL,3,CRats on the rise after wet weather
OL,5,FPaul Blackhurst, from Rentokil, said:
OL,6,F"Rats are highly capable swimmers.
OL,7,FThey can navigate strong currents,
OL,8,Fenter exposed pipes and sewers, and
OL,9,Fswim considerable distances in open
OL,10,Fwater.
OL,12,F"However, what they cannot tolerate is
OL,13,Fprolonged submersion. When burrow
OL,14,Fsystems and sewer networks flood, rats
OL,15,Fare forced to seek higher, drier
OL,16,Fground, increasing the risk of
OL,17,Finfestations in properties.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/4
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
