FL,365,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F364A1772471476
OL,3,CRats on the rise after wet weather
OL,5,F"With northern regions already
OL,6,Freporting notable increases in
OL,7,Freported activity, continued wet
OL,8,Fweather may push more rats into
OL,9,Fproperties. Early prevention and
OL,10,Fprofessional support are key."
OL,12,FTo reduce the risk of rodents, people
OL,13,Fare being encouraged to clear any
OL,14,Fdebris near properties, seal potential
OL,15,Fentry points and ensure bins are
OL,16,Ffitted with tight lids.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/4
